window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>A Reader's Favorite Award-Winning Novel.</i></b></p> <p><b>When Nathan Stryder is abducted from Earth and thrown headfirst into an interstellar war, it shatters his world.</b></p> <p>Freed from his captors by the Meraki Dominya, Nathan discovers a chilling truth: his sister has also been taken. Desperate to find her, he joins the Meraki and is partnered with Arista, an elite commando trained to kill first and <i>not </i>ask questions later.</p> <p>As Nathan learns to survive a galaxy at war, a quiet, undeniable bond develops with Arista—complicated by duty, danger, and everything they stand to lose. Amid this chaos, he uncovers a kindred spirit beneath her hardened exterior and sparks ignite between them. But in a war written in the stars, the heart’s path is never simple.</p> <p>Pulled into a galaxy-wide conflict that challenges everything he believes, Nathan must confront danger, betrayal, and secrets that could change the fate of worlds. With the future of a planet hanging in the balance, can he survive this cosmic storm and save his sister?</p> <p><b>A sweeping, character-driven space opera—rich with action, layered characters, and high-stakes conflict—anchored by a slow-burning connection that unfolds across the trilogy.</b><br> <br> Fans of Mass Effect, Rachel Bach’s <i>Fortune’s Pawn</i>, The Expanse, and Jessie Mihalik​​​​​​​ will be drawn to this epic tale of courage, trust, and hope in a galaxy on the brink.</p>"; 
